⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Boxer
node AFM · AFM · ⟦Boxer:AFM:df4b50⟧

WHO   — Boxer — the loyal worker
WHAT  — The betrayed proletariat: he carries the windmill on his back and is sold to the knacker the moment he collapses.
WHERE — AFM · ANIMAL FARM  Framework inputs: Animal Farm (George Orwell, 1945)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the revolution runs on the loyalty of the workers it will ultimately discard — Boxer is its tragedy made flesh.
HOW   — By endless labour and uncritical faith, and a final cart-ride to the glue-maker dressed up by Squealer as a hospital.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I only ever said ‘I will work harder’ and ‘Napoleon is always right’ — and for that faith they sold my body for a case of whisky.

